HEADWORD: Parusia
<hw>Pa*ru"si*a</hw> <pr>(p⟦adot⟧*r⟦udd⟧"zh⟦icr⟧*⟦adot⟧)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr. Gr. <grk>paroysi`a</grk> presence, fr.
<grk>parei^nai</grk> to be present; <grk>para`</grk> beside +
<grk>e'i^nai</grk> to be.]</ety> <fld>(Rhet.)</fld> <def>A figure of
speech by which the present tense is used instead of the past or the
future, as in the animated narration of past, or in the prediction of
future, events.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

